"""Frontend 1 — trame + pyvista (server-side VTK rendering).

This UI calls the Python ``core`` DIRECTLY (trame is server-side); it does NOT go
through the HTTP API for compute. It reaches feature parity with the React
frontend and adds the full clinician workflow:

  * Controls are generated by iterating the parameter registry (``control_specs``)
    — the param list is never hardcoded, so the two UIs cannot drift.
  * A SIDE selector driven purely by ``session.sides`` (``['full']`` for a single
    scan, ``['left','right']`` for a bilateral one — never assumes a bone).
  * An "Apply / Recompute" button re-runs ``core.pipeline`` with the CURRENT
    parameter values and swaps in the freshly computed geometry.
  * A Mode A / Mode B toggle. Mode A = single-side cortical thickness. Mode B adds
    a per-side THICKNESS view AND a two-side signed-DEVIATION view.
  * SHARE panel + UI SWITCHER: reads runtime config (``outputs/public_urls.json``)
    and shows the current public URL plus a button to jump to the OTHER UI.
  * UPLOAD (all formats): ``.zip .nii .nii.gz .stl .ply .obj .vtp`` — branches on
    the result (mesh session => view/compare only, single-sided => a "Full"
    selector, bilateral => Left/Right).
  * HOVER TOOLTIP: hovering the 3D surface reads the picked point's scalar
    (thickness_mm / deviation_mm, mm) + position, with a local readout vs the
    map mean.
  * EXPORT panel: pick formats (png/tiff/jpg/stl/ply/obj/vtp/dicom), a DPI, and a
    camera pose (azimuth/elevation/roll/zoom) -> ``core.export.export_bundle`` ->
    real per-format download links.
  * MANUAL ANCHOR (Mode B): translation x/y/z mm + rotation deg (a 4x4 nudge) plus
    a reference/target swap ("which side on top"), recomputed on apply.

Heavy compute runs on a background thread so the server stays responsive.

Run:  .venv/bin/python -m app_trame.app   (serves on http://localhost:8081)
"""

